L = np.ones((256,256,1))*75
A = np.tile(np.arange(-127, 128+1).reshape((-1, 1)), (1,256))
B = np.flip(A.transpose(), 0)
LAB_base = np.concatenate((L,np.expand_dims(A,2),np.expand_dims(B,2)), axis=2)
RGB_base = color.lab2rgb(LAB_base)

alpha = np.expand_dims(np.sum(hist, axis=0).reshape((256,256,1)),2)
alpha[alpha>0] = 1
alpha = (alpha + 0.25) / 1.25
RGBA = np.concatenate((RGB_base, alpha), axis=2)
plt.imshow(np.flip(RGBA, 1))
plt.show()

fig = plt.figure()

def genRGBA(frame_ix, bg=0.25):
    alpha = hist[frame_ix,:].toarray().reshape((256, 256, 1))
    alpha[alpha>0] = 1 # threshold such that any presence is shown
    alpha = (alpha + bg) / (1 + bg) # boost all colours such that we have a background
    RGBA = np.concatenate((RGB_base, alpha), axis=2)
    return np.flip(RGBA, 1)
    
def updatefig(frame_ix):
    im[0].set_array(genRGBA(frame_ix))
    
    cap.set(1, frame_ix);
    ret, frame = cap.read()
    im[1].set_array(frame)
    
    return im

ax1 = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 1)
ax2 = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 2)

im = [0,0]
im[0] = ax1.imshow(RGB_base, animated=True)
ax1.axis('off')
im[1] = ax2.imshow(RGB_base, animated=True)
ax2.axis('off')

ani = animation.FuncAnimation(fig, updatefig, frames=range(0,hist.shape[0],100), interval=50, blit=True)

from ipywidgets import interact, interactive, fixed, interact_manual
import ipywidgets as widgets

def avgcol_frame(ix, l = 50):
    _, cols = hist[ix, :].nonzero()
    if len(cols) < 1:
        return np.array([l, 0, 0])
    indices2d = np.array([(a-offset, b-offset) for a,b in zip(*np.unravel_index(cols, (256,256)))])
    counts = np.array(hist[ix, :][0,cols].toarray().tolist()[0])
    total = np.sum(indices2d * counts[:,np.newaxis],0)
    return np.append([l], total / np.sum(counts))

def update(ix):
    fig3 = plt.figure()
    axs1 = fig3.add_subplot(2, 1, 1)
    axs2 = fig3.add_subplot(2, 2, 3)
    axs3 = fig3.add_subplot(2, 2, 4)

    cap.set(1, ix);
    ret, frame = cap.read()
    axs1.imshow(frame, animated=True)
    axs1.axis('off')
    axs2.imshow(genRGBA(ix))
    axs2.axis('off')   
    avg_colour = np.tile(color.lab2rgb(avgcol_frame(ix).reshape((1,1,3))), (100, 100, 1))
    axs3.imshow(avg_colour)
    axs3.axis('off')
    plt.show()
    
a = interact(update, ix=widgets.IntSlider(value=ix,
                                               continuous_update=False,
                                               min=0,
                                               max=total_frames,
                                               step=100))

steps = range(0,int(total_frames), 100)
